ially, as some agents may demonstrate a prolonged elimination half-life. For example, a 5-week washout period is typically recommended following use of fluoxetine and 2 weeks following use of MAOIs before administering another serotonergic agent. If serotonin syndrome develops or is suspected during the course of therapy, all serotonergic agents should be discontinued immediately and supportive care rendered as necessary.', 'Metabolism, Synergism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317475);
